{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27055649-4a22-4ce2-90f7-ad9cc9fd8356","content":"In .NET MAUI, lifecycle management moved from `Application` to `Window`. Override `CreateWindow` in your `App` class and subscribe to window lifecycle events:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => { /* OnStart equivalent */ };\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep equivalent */ };\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* OnResume equivalent */ };\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Mapping:**\n| Xamarin.Forms | .NET MAUI Window Event |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart` | `Created` |\n| `OnSleep` | `Stopped` |\n| `OnResume` | `Resumed` |\n\nAlternatively, subclass `Window` and override `OnCreated()`, `OnStopped()`, `OnResumed()` for a cleaner separation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a6ec754-2b85-400f-8124-7ec3ce463688","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a straightforward knowledge question about the MAUI lifecycle API.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` in your `Application` class. In .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. You now use the `Window` lifecycle events or the `ILifecycleEventHandler` approach.\n\nSpecifically, in .NET MAUI:\n- The `Application` class still exists but the recommended approach is to use **Window lifecycle events** via `CreateWindow` or by subscribing to lifecycle events on the `Window` object.\n\n\n- You can override `CreateWindow()` to attach event handlers to your Window, or leverage platform-specific lifecycle events.\n\nThe mapping looks like this: `OnStart` maps to `Window.Created` or a custom `OnCreated` override, `OnSleep` corresponds to `Window.Deactivated` or `Window.Stopped`, and `OnResume` aligns with `Window.Activated` or `Window.Resumed`. The shift in .NET MAUI moved away from Application-level lifecycle methods toward a Window-centric model. I'm showing how to hook into these lifecycle events by overriding `CreateWindow` in the `App` class and subscribing to the window events for each lifecycle stage.","outputTokens":883,"requestId":"080C:348511:A80893:C226D6:69F2A90B"},"id":"a404bd00-32ff-46e7-96f1-b4d58c0d3d67","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:58:02.832Z","parentId":"5999c415-6be8-4ac9-a366-c4fdf4700861"}
